session_history.content: educate yourself on the table dds of fitness_db

The fitness_db database contains the following tables: Products, SaleDetails, ServiceTickets, Sales, and Customers, each with its respective schema as defined in the provided DDL statements.

Key Observations

  • The Products table stores information about the fitness products, including ProductID, ProductName, ProductType, Brand, Price, and StockQuantity.
  • The SaleDetails table records the details of each sale, referencing the SaleID from the Sales table and ProductID from the Products table.
  • The ServiceTickets table tracks customer service requests, linking to the Customers and Products tables via CustomerID and ProductID respectively.
  • The Sales table stores sales transactions, including CustomerID, SaleDate, TotalAmount, and SalesPersonID, with a foreign key relationship to the Customers table.
  • The Customers table holds customer information such as FirstName, LastName, Email, Phone, Address, City, State, ZipCode, and RegistrationDate.
  • Foreign key constraints enforce relationships between tables, ensuring data integrity (e.g., SaleDetails referencing Sales and Products).

SQL DDL: fitness_db.Products 
CREATE MULTISET TABLE fitness_db.Products ,FALLBACK ,
     NO BEFORE JOURNAL,
     NO AFTER JOURNAL,
     CHECKSUM = DEFAULT,
     DEFAULT MERGEBLOCKRATIO,
     MAP = TD_MAP1
     (
      ProductID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      ProductName VARCHAR(100) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC NOT NULL,
      ProductType VARCHAR(50) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,
      Brand VARCHAR(50) CHARACTER SET LATIN NOT CASESPECIFIC,
      Price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
      StockQuantity INTEGER)
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( ProductID );
SQL DDL: fitness_db.SaleDetails 
CREATE MULTISET TABLE fitness_db.SaleDetails ,FALLBACK ,
     NO BEFORE JOURNAL,
     NO AFTER JOURNAL,
     CHECKSUM = DEFAULT,
     DEFAULT MERGEBLOCKRATIO,
     MAP = TD_MAP1
     (
      SaleDetailID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      SaleID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      ProductID INTEGER NOT NULL,
      Quantity INTEGER NOT NULL,
      UnitPrice DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL, 
FOREIGN KEY ( SaleID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Sales ( SaleID ),
FOREIGN KEY ( ProductID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Products ( ProductID ))
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( SaleDetailID );

     (

FOREIGN KEY ( CustomerID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Customers ( CustomerID ),
FOREIGN KEY ( ProductID ) REFERENCES fitness_db.Products ( ProductID ))
UNIQUE PRIMARY INDEX ( TicketID );

     (
